				\begin{document}$$ 1/3\,(\Updelta \delta C^{\alpha }_{{i - 1}} \, + \,\Updelta \delta C^{\alpha }_{i} \, + \,\Updelta \delta C^{\alpha }_{{i + 1}} \, - \,\Updelta \delta C^{\beta }_{{i - 1}} \, - \,\Updelta \delta C^{\beta }_{i} \, - \,\Updelta \delta C^{\beta }_{{i + 1}}) $$\end{document} (Metzler et al. 1993). A positive value for Δδi indicates that the residue i is located in a regular helical structure, while a negative value indicates that it is located in a regular β-strand. The tentative positions of regular secondary structures, which are identified at the bottom of the figure, were obtained with the criterion that |Δδi| ≥ 1 for three or more sequentially adjacent residues. No information is as yet available on the assembly of the β-strands into β-sheets.
